        "answer_count": 3,
        "title": "How to toString() a List like this one : List&lt;Option&gt;?",
        "body": "<p>Suppose I have a <code>list<\/code> of an object called <code>Option<\/code> : <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;Option&gt; opts = ArrayList&lt;Option&gt;();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have override <code>toString()<\/code> for the object <code>Option<\/code>.  <\/p>\n\n<p>when I do <code>opts.toString()<\/code> that means I do toString for a List , I get some unnecessary commas <strong>,,,,,<\/strong>. <\/p>\n\n<p>I would like to change that. Please, is there a way better then for-looping inside the List to toString each element ? Hope I am clear.  <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 30936112,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "arraylist",
            "java-8",
            "tostring"
        ],
